# Testing Guidelines

Use this rule with `.ai/lifecycle/plan.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/test.md`, and `.ai/lifecycle/ship.md`.

## Framework
This project uses **{{testFramework}}** for testing.

{{> testCommands }}

## Unit Tests
- Co-locate unit tests with the code they are testing (e.g. `user.service.spec.ts` next to `user.service.ts`).
{{#if isNestJS}}
- Use NestJS `TestBed` to create isolated testing modules.
- Mock all repository and external service dependencies using standard `jest.mock()` or custom mock providers in the TestBed.
{{else if isExpress}}
- Use a mock HTTP `req` and `res` object when testing controllers directly.
{{else if isFastify}}
- Use `fastify.inject()` to test route handlers without listening on a port.
{{else if isHono}}
- Use Hono's `app.request()` for lightweight integration & unit testing.
{{/if}}

## E2E Tests
- Place e2e tests in the `test/` directory at the project root.
- E2E tests should spin up the full application and hit a real (test-specific) database.
- Clear the database between test runs using a teardown script or `beforeEach` hook.

## Mocking Conventions
- Only mock external boundaries (databases, 3rd party APIs, queues).
- Do not over-mock internal business logic if testing it all together is fast and deterministic.

## JSDoc and Documentation
- Clearly comment complex test setups.
- Use the `Arrange, Act, Assert` pattern in every test block.

## Lifecycle Expectations

- Plan tests before implementation for non-trivial backend changes.
- Use targeted checks for narrow changes, then broaden when public APIs, data, auth, integrations, async behavior, or generated output changes.
- Include manual QA when automation does not cover migrations, provider behavior, deployment order, or adapter output.

## Must Avoid

- Unit-only validation for public contract, migration, auth, or integration changes.
- Skipping validation failure, auth denial, not-found, provider failure, retry, and duplicate-delivery paths when relevant.
- Tests that assert implementation details instead of observable behavior.
- Claiming adapter or generated-output checks passed without inspecting generated files.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Tests match backend risk and changed behavior.
- Success and material failure paths are covered.
- Skipped or missing checks are called out.
- Build, unit/integration/e2e, migration, smoke, and manual checks are recorded when relevant.
